{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016xZNteQag7KYj8vHVTuy82","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Cloche System Design\n     2â†’\n     3â†’## Overview\n     4â†’\n     5â†’Cloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     6â†’environments for coding agents to operate in isolation, a workflow DSL for linking\n     7â†’agentic and script-driven tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n     8â†’\n     9â†’This document describes the architecture for the MVP (v0.1).\n    10â†’\n    11â†’## System Components\n    12â†’\n    13â†’Cloche is a Go monorepo producing three binaries:\n    14â†’\n    15â†’```\n    16â†’cmd/\n    17â†’  cloche/         # CLI client (short-lived)\n    18â†’  cloched/        # Daemon/orchestrator (long-running)\n    19â†’  cloche-agent/   # In-container entrypoint (autonomous)\n    20â†’```\n    21â†’\n    22â†’### cloche (CLI)\n    23â†’\n    24â†’Short-lived process. Talks to `cloched` over gRPC (Unix socket locally, TCP remotely).\n    25â†’\n    26â†’Subcommands:\n    27â†’- `run <workflow>` â€” Launch a new workflow run\n    28â†’- `status [run-id]` â€” Check run status\n    29â†’- `logs <run-id>` â€” Stream logs from a running workflow (bidirectional gRPC stream)\n    30â†’- `stop <run-id>` â€” Cancel a running workflow (signals container with SIGTERM)\n    31â†’\n    32â†’Accepts prompt files or stdin input for user commands.\n    33â†’\n    34â†’### cloched (Daemon)\n    35â†’\n    36â†’Long-running process. Responsibilities:\n    37â†’- Launch and manage Docker containers for workflow runs\n    38â†’- Listen to status streams from running agents\n    39â†’- Record captures (step inputs, outputs, results, logs)\n    40â†’- Expose gRPC API for the CLI\n    41â†’- Persist state via pluggable storage (SQLite initially)\n    42â†’\n    43â†’The daemon does NOT interpret workflow logic. It knows \"container X is running workflow Y\"\n    44â†’and collects status. The agent is self-directing.\n    45â†’\n    46â†’### cloche-agent (In-Container Runtime)\n    47â†’\n    48â†’Autonomous process running inside the Docker container. Responsibilities:\n    49â†’- Parse the workflow DSL (workflow files live in the codebase)\n    50â†’- Walk the workflow graph, executing steps and following results\n    51â†’- Invoke coding agents (Claude Code, custom commands) and scripts\n    52â†’- Stream structured status events back to `cloched`\n    53â†’- Run to completion (`done` or `abort`) without human intervention\n    54â†’\n    55â†’The agent is told which workflow to execute at launch. It handles everything else.\n    56â†’\n    57â†’## Communication\n    58â†’\n    59â†’### CLI <-> Daemon: gRPC\n    60â†’\n    61â†’- Protobuf contracts define the API (the API is the spec)\n    62â†’- Bidirectional streaming for `logs` (tail container output in real-time)\n    63â†’- Unix socket for local communication, TCP for remote\n    64â†’\n    65â†’### Agent <-> Daemon: Structured JSON over stdout\n    66â†’\n    67â†’- The agent writes JSON-lines to stdout with status updates\n    68â†’- `cloched` attaches to the container's stdout stream via Docker API\n    69â†’- Messages include: step started, step completed (with result name), logs, errors\n    70â†’- Kill/cancel: daemon sends SIGTERM to container, agent handles graceful shutdown\n    71â†’\n    72â†’## Workflow DSL\n    73â†’\n    74â†’### Vocabulary\n    75â†’\n    76â†’| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n    77â†’|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n    78â†’| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    79â†’| step     | A unit of work (type: `agent` or `script`)                         |\n    80â†’| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    81â†’| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step                              |\n    82â†’| done     | Built-in terminal step indicating successful completion            |\n    83â†’| abort    | Built-in terminal step indicating failure (reports error and exits)|\n    84â†’\n    85â†’### Syntax\n    86â†’\n    87â†’```\n    88â†’workflow \"implement-feature\" {\n    89â†’  step code {\n    90â†’    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    91â†’    container {\n    92â†’      image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    93â†’      network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"internal-docs.company.com\"]\n    94â†’    }\n    95â†’    results = [success, fail, retry_with_feedback]\n    96â†’  }\n    97â†’\n    98â†’  step check {\n    99â†’    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n   100â†’    results = [pass, fail]\n   101â†’  }\n   102â†’\n   103â†’  step review {\n   104â†’    prompt = file(\"prompts/review.md\")\n   105â†’    input = step.code.output\n   106â†’    results = [approved, changes_requested]\n   107â†’  }\n   108â†’\n   109â†’  code:success -> check\n   110â†’  code:fail -> abort\n   111â†’  code:retry_with_feedback -> code\n   112â†’\n   113â†’  check:pass -> review\n   114â†’  check:fail -> code:retry_with_feedback\n   115â†’\n   116â†’  review:approved -> done\n   117â†’  review:changes_requested -> code\n   118â†’}\n   119â†’```\n   120â†’\n   121â†’### Key Properties\n   122â†’\n   123â†’- Step type is inferred from content: `prompt` field â†’ agent step, `run` field â†’ script step.\n   124â†’- Steps declare which results they can emit. The step decides at runtime which result to report.\n   125â†’- Wiring is separate from step definitions. This enables runtime injection of new steps\n   126â†’  (the self-evolution feature) â€” insert a new check between existing steps by rewiring,\n   127â†’  without modifying either step.\n   128â†’- `file()` loads external content (prompt files, scripts).\n   129â†’- Step inputs can reference other step outputs (`step.code.output`).\n   130â†’- The graph engine validates at parse time: all declared results are wired, no orphan steps,\n   131â†’  entry point exists.\n   132â†’\n   133â†’## Hexagonal Architecture\n   134â†’\n   135â†’The core domain is independent of Docker, gRPC, SQLite, or any other infrastructure.\n   136â†’\n   137â†’### Domain\n   138â†’\n   139â†’```\n   140â†’internal/domain/\n   141â†’  workflow.go    # Workflow, Step, Result, Graph types\n   142â†’  run.go         # Run, RunState, StepExecution types\n   143â†’  capture.go     # CapturedInput, CapturedOutput for replay\n   144â†’```\n   145â†’\n   146â†’### Ports (interfaces)\n   147â†’\n   148â†’```\n   149â†’internal/ports/\n   150â†’  store.go       # RunStore, WorkflowStore, CaptureStore\n   151â†’  container.go   # ContainerRuntime (start, stop, attach, logs)\n   152â†’  agent.go       # AgentAdapter (how to invoke an agent)\n   153â†’  notifier.go    # StatusNotifier (how to report progress)\n   154â†’```\n   155â†’\n   156â†’### Adapters (implementations)\n   157â†’\n   158â†’```\n   159â†’internal/adapters/\n   160â†’  docker/        # ContainerRuntime via Docker API\n   161â†’  sqlite/        # Store implementations via SQLite\n   162â†’  grpc/          # gRPC server (daemon) and client (CLI)\n   163â†’  agents/\n   164â†’    claudecode/  # AgentAdapter for Claude Code\n   165â†’    generic/     # AgentAdapter for arbitrary commands\n   166â†’```\n   167â†’\n   168â†’### Key Interfaces\n   169â†’\n   170â†’- **ContainerRuntime** â€” Start/stop containers, attach to stdout, copy files in/out.\n   171â†’  Docker today, Podman or Firecracker later.\n   172â†’- **RunStore** â€” Persist run state (active step, reported results, timestamps).\n   173â†’- **CaptureStore** â€” Store step inputs/outputs for replay. Git refs serve as pointers\n   174â†’  to file states; metadata lives in the store.\n   175â†’- **AgentAdapter** â€” Translates between Cloche's step protocol and a specific agent's\n   176â†’  interface. Claude Code adapter knows how to invoke `claude` CLI. Generic adapter runs\n   177â†’  any command.\n   178â†’- **StatusNotifier** â€” How the agent reports progress. Stdout JSON-lines initially.\n   179â†’\n   180â†’## Container Model\n   181â†’\n   182â†’### One Container Per Workflow Run\n   183â†’\n   184â†’A container is spun up for a workflow run. All steps execute inside the same container.\n   185â†’File state accumulates naturally across steps (agent modifies code, then test script\n   186â†’runs against those modifications).\n   187â†’\n   188â†’### Lifecycle\n   189â†’\n   190â†’1. `cloched` pulls/builds the container image\n   191â†’2. Copies project files into the container at `/workspace`\n   192â†’3. Starts the container with `cloche-agent` as entrypoint, passing the workflow name\n   193â†’4. `cloche-agent` parses the workflow, walks the graph, executes steps\n   194â†’5. Agent streams status events to `cloched` via stdout\n   195â†’6. At step boundaries, modified files are pushed to the host via git (agent-specific branch)\n   196â†’7. On completion (`done`/`abort`), container is stopped\n   197â†’\n   198â†’### File Extraction via Git\n   199â†’\n   200â†’The container's git remote is configured to push to the host repository. Each run pushes\n   201â†’to a unique branch (e.g. `cloche/run-<id>/step-<name>`). This provides:\n   202â†’- Full git history of what the agent did\n   203â†’- Trivial diffs between input and output states\n   204â†’- Clean branch-per-step organization\n   205â†’- No bind mounts (maintains isolation)\n   206â†’\n   207â†’### Security Boundaries\n   208â†’\n   209â†’1. **Filesystem** â€” No access beyond `/workspace`. Copy-in at start, git push for extraction.\n   210â†’2. **Network** â€” `--network none` by default. If `network_allow` is specified, Cloche creates\n   211â†’   a custom Docker network restricting egress to allowlisted domains via DNS proxy.\n   212â†’3. **Environment** â€” Configured in Dockerfile/image. Cloche does not inject env vars.\n   213â†’\n   214â†’## Capture System\n   215â†’\n   216â†’Each step execution is captured for later inspection and replay.\n   217â†’\n   218â†’### What Gets Captured\n   219â†’\n   220â†’- Step config (prompt, type, container settings)\n   221â†’- Input state (git ref of what was provided to the step)\n   222â†’- Output state (git ref of what the step produced)\n   223â†’- Result reported (which result name)\n   224â†’- Stdout/stderr logs\n   225â†’- Timing metadata\n   226â†’\n   227â†’### Storage\n   228â†’\n   229â†’Metadata in the store (SQLite initially). Git refs serve as pointers to actual file\n   230â†’states â€” no duplication of file content.\n   231â†’\n   232â†’## MVP Scope (v0.1)\n   233â†’\n   234â†’### In Scope\n   235â†’\n   236â†’- `cloche` CLI: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`\n   237â†’- `cloched` daemon: container lifecycle, status collection, gRPC API, SQLite store\n   238â†’- `cloche-agent`: DSL parser, graph engine, agent/script execution, status reporting\n   239â†’- Workflow DSL: steps, results, wiring, `done`/`abort` terminals, `file()` references\n   240â†’- Container model: Docker, copy-in project files, git push for extraction, network allowlist\n   241â†’- Agent adapters: Generic (run a command) + Claude Code\n   242â†’- Capture system: Record step inputs/outputs/results\n   243â†’\n   244â†’### Post-MVP\n   245â†’\n   246â†’- Self-evolution: failure pattern analysis, automatic step injection into workflows\n   247â†’- Replay system: partial/full/dry replay of captured runs\n   248â†’- Auto-split commits into stacked branches\n   249â†’- Additional agent adapters\n   250â†’- Alternative storage backends (Postgres, DynamoDB)\n   251â†’- Alternative container runtimes (Podman, Firecracker)\n   252â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"76c245ca-f0a2-4e35-9168-5516b247e99a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XRVRpqvEB56BukVSQmDx21","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’package grpc\n     2â†’\n     3â†’import (\n     4â†’\t\"bufio\"\n     5â†’\t\"context\"\n     6â†’\t\"encoding/json\"\n     7â†’\t\"fmt\"\n     8â†’\t\"log\"\n     9â†’\t\"os\"\n    10â†’\t\"os/exec\"\n    11â†’\t\"path/filepath\"\n    12â†’\t\"strings\"\n    13â†’\t\"sync\"\n    14â†’\t\"time\"\n    15â†’\n    16â†’\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n    17â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/docker\"\n    18â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/web\"\n    19â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/config\"\n    20â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    21â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/evolution\"\n    22â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/host\"\n    23â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    24â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    25â†’\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n    26â†’\trpcgrpc \"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n    27â†’\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/metadata\"\n    28â†’)\n    29â†’\n    30â†’type ClocheServer struct {\n    31â†’\tpb.UnimplementedClocheServiceServer\n    32â†’\tstore        ports.RunStore\n    33â†’\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n    34â†’\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n    35â†’\tcontainer    ports.ContainerRuntime\n    36â†’\tdefaultImage string\n    37â†’\tevolution    *evolution.Trigger\n    38â†’\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    39â†’\tshutdownFn   func()\n    40â†’\tmu           sync.Mutex\n    41â†’\trunIDs       map[string]string      // run_id -> container_id\n    42â†’\tloops        map[string]*host.Loop  // project_dir -> orchestration loop\n    43â†’}\n    44â†’\n    45â†’func NewClocheServer(store ports.RunStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime) *ClocheServer {\n    46â†’\treturn &ClocheServer{\n    47â†’\t\tstore:     store,\n    48â†’\t\tcontainer: container,\n    49â†’\t\trunIDs:    make(map[string]string),\n    50â†’\t\tloops:     make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n    51â†’\t}\n    52â†’}\n    53â†’\n    54â†’func NewClocheServerWithCaptures(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime, defaultImage string) *ClocheServer {\n    55â†’\treturn &ClocheServer{\n    56â†’\t\tstore:        store,\n    57â†’\t\tcaptures:     captures,\n    58â†’\t\tcontainer:    container,\n    59â†’\t\tdefaultImage: defaultImage,\n    60â†’\t\trunIDs:       make(map[string]string),\n    61â†’\t\tloops:        make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n    62â†’\t}\n    63â†’}\n    64â†’\n    65â†’// SetLogStore attaches a log store to the server for indexing extracted log files.\n    66â†’func (s *ClocheServer) SetLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) {\n    67â†’\ts.logStore = ls\n    68â†’}\n    69â†’\n    70â†’\n    71â†’// SetEvolution attaches an evolution trigger to the server.\n    72â†’func (s *ClocheServer) SetEvolution(trigger *evolution.Trigger) {\n    73â†’\ts.evolution = trigger\n    74â†’}\n    75â†’\n    76â†’// SetLogBroadcaster attaches a log broadcaster for live-streaming LLM output.\n    77â†’func (s *ClocheServer) SetLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) {\n    78â†’\ts.logBroadcast = b\n    79â†’}\n    80â†’\n    81â†’// SetShutdownFunc sets the callback invoked when the Shutdown RPC is called.\n    82â†’func (s *ClocheServer) SetShutdownFunc(fn func()) {\n    83â†’\ts.shutdownFn = fn\n    84â†’}\n    85â†’\n    86â†’func (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n    87â†’\tif s.container == nil {\n    88â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n    89â†’\t}\n    90â†’\n    91â†’\t// Generate a unique run ID, retrying on collision\n    92â†’\tvar runID string\n    93â†’\tfor attempts := 0; attempts < 10; attempts++ {\n    94â†’\t\trunID = domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n    95â†’\t\texisting, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n    96â†’\t\tif err != nil {\n    97â†’\t\t\tbreak // ID is free\n    98â†’\t\t}\n    99â†’\t\t// Reuse if completed more than 1 hour ago\n   100â†’\t\tif !existing.CompletedAt.IsZero() && time.Since(existing.CompletedAt) > time.Hour {\n   101â†’\t\t\t_ = s.store.DeleteRun(ctx, runID)\n   102â†’\t\t\tbreak\n   103â†’\t\t}\n   104â†’\t}\n   105â†’\n   106â†’\t// Write prompt to .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt (run-specific to avoid conflicts)\n   107â†’\tif req.Prompt != \"\" {\n   108â†’\t\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(req.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID)\n   109â†’\t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(clocheDir, 0755); err != nil {\n   110â†’\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating .cloche dir: %w\", err)\n   111â†’\t\t}\n   112â†’\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"prompt.txt\"), []byte(req.Prompt), 0644); err != nil {\n   113â†’\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"writing prompt: %w\", err)\n   114â†’\t\t}\n   115â†’\t}\n   116â†’\trun := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\n   117â†’\trun.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\n   118â†’\trun.Title = req.Title\n   119â†’\tif err := s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run); err != nil {\n   120â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating run: %w\", err)\n   121â†’\t}\n   122â†’\n   123â†’\t// Resolve image: request-level override, then server default\n   124â†’\timage := req.Image\n   125â†’\tif image == \"\" {\n   126â†’\t\timage = s.defaultImage\n   127â†’\t}\n   128â†’\n   129â†’\t// Launch container start + tracking in background so the RPC returns immediately.\n   130â†’\t// The run stays in \"pending\" state until the container is up.\n   131â†’\tgo s.launchAndTrack(runID, image, req.KeepContainer, req)\n   132â†’\n   133â†’\treturn &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n   134â†’}\n   135â†’\n   136â†’// launchAndTrack starts the container and then tracks it to completion.\n   137â†’// It runs in a background goroutine with its own context, independent of the\n   138â†’// RPC context which may be cancelled after RunWorkflow returns.\n   139â†’func (s *ClocheServer) launchAndTrack(runID, image string, keepContainer bool, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) {\n   140â†’\tctx := context.Background()\n   141â†’\n   142â†’\t// Auto-rebuild image if the project Dockerfile has changed since last build.\n   143â†’\tif ensurer, ok := s.container.(ports.ImageEnsurer); ok {\n   144â†’\t\tif err := ensurer.EnsureImage(ctx, req.ProjectDir, image); err != nil {\n   145â†’\t\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   146â†’\t\t\tif run != nil {\n   147â†’\t\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to ensure image: %v\", err))\n   148â†’\t\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   149â†’\t\t\t}\n   150â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to ensure image: %v\", runID, err)\n   151â†’\t\t\t\treturn\n   152â†’\t\t}\n   153â†’\t}\n   154â†’\n   155â†’\tbaseSHA := gitHEAD(req.ProjectDir)\n   156â†’\n   157â†’\tcontainerID, err := s.container.Start(ctx, ports.ContainerConfig{\n   158â†’\t\tImage:        image,\n   159â†’\t\tWorkflowName: req.WorkflowName,\n   160â†’\t\tProjectDir:   req.ProjectDir,\n   161â†’\t\tRunID:        runID,\n   162â†’\t\tNetworkAllow: []string{\"*\"},\n   163â†’\t})\n   164â†’\tif err != nil {\n   165â†’\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   166â†’\t\tif run != nil {\n   167â†’\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to start container: %v\", err))\n   168â†’\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   169â†’\t\t}\n   170â†’\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to start container: %v\", runID, err)\n   171â†’\t\treturn\n   172â†’\t}\n   173â†’\n   174â†’\ts.mu.Lock()\n   175â†’\ts.runIDs[runID] = containerID\n   176â†’\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   177â†’\n   178â†’\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   179â†’\tif run != nil {\n   180â†’\t\trun.Start()\n   181â†’\t\trun.ContainerID = containerID\n   182â†’\t\trun.BaseSHA = baseSHA\n   183â†’\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   184â†’\t}\n   185â†’\n   186â†’\ts.trackRun(runID, containerID, req.ProjectDir, req.WorkflowName, keepContainer)\n   187â†’}\n   188â†’\n   189â†’func (s *ClocheServer) trackRun(runID, containerID, projectDir, workflowName string, keepContainer bool) {\n   190â†’\tctx := context.Background()\n   191â†’\n   192â†’\t// Attach to agent output\n   193â†’\treader, err := s.container.AttachOutput(ctx, containerID)\n   194â†’\tif err != nil {\n   195â†’\t\tlog.Printf(\"failed to attach to output for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n   196â†’\t\t\treturn\n   197â†’\t}\n   198â†’\n   199â†’\t// Parse JSON-lines status messages\n   200â†’\tvar reportedResult string // captured from MsgRunCompleted, persisted after branch extraction\n   201â†’\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(reader)\n   202â†’\tscanner.Buffer(make([]byte, 0, 256*1024), 1024*1024) // 1MB max to handle large log messages\n   203â†’\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n   204â†’\t\tvar msg protocol.StatusMessage\n   205â†’\t\tif err := json.Unmarshal(scanner.Bytes(), &msg); err != nil {\n   206â†’\t\t\tcontinue\n   207â†’\t\t}\n   208â†’\n   209â†’\t\t// Fast path: log messages don't need store interaction.\n   210â†’\t\tif msg.Type == protocol.MsgLog {\n   211â†’\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   212â†’\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   213â†’\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   214â†’\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"llm\",\n   215â†’\t\t\t\t\tContent:   msg.Message,\n   216â†’\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   217â†’\t\t\t\t})\n   218â†’\t\t\t}\n   219â†’\t\t\tcontinue\n   220â†’\t\t}\n   221â†’\n   222â†’\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   223â†’\t\tif err != nil {\n   224â†’\t\t\tcontinue\n   225â†’\t\t}\n   226â†’\n   227â†’\t\tswitch msg.Type {\n   228â†’\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepStarted:\n   229â†’\t\t\trun.RecordStepStart(msg.StepName)\n   230â†’\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n   231â†’\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n   232â†’\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   233â†’\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n   234â†’\t\t\t\t})\n   235â†’\t\t\t}\n   236â†’\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   237â†’\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   238â†’\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   239â†’\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n   240â†’\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_started: \" + msg.StepName,\n   241â†’\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   242â†’\t\t\t\t})\n   243â†’\t\t\t}\n   244â†’\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepCompleted:\n   245â†’\t\t\trun.RecordStepComplete(msg.StepName, msg.Result)\n   246â†’\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n   247â†’\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n   248â†’\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    msg.StepName,\n   249â†’\t\t\t\t\tResult:      msg.Result,\n   250â†’\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n   251â†’\t\t\t\t})\n   252â†’\t\t\t}\n   253â†’\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   254â†’\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   255â†’\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   256â†’\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n   257â†’\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_completed: \" + msg.StepName + \" -> \" + msg.Result,\n   258â†’\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   259â†’\t\t\t\t})\n   260â†’\t\t\t}\n   261â†’\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunTitle:\n   262â†’\t\t\tif run.Title == \"\" {\n   263â†’\t\t\t\trun.Title = msg.Message\n   264â†’\t\t\t}\n   265â†’\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunCompleted:\n   266â†’\t\t\treportedResult = msg.Result\n   267â†’\t\t\tcontinue // Don't persist terminal state yet; branch extraction must finish first\n   268â†’\t\t}\n   269â†’\n   270â†’\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   271â†’\t}\n   272â†’\treader.Close()\n   273â†’\n   274â†’\t// Signal live-stream subscribers that this run is done.\n   275â†’\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   276â†’\t\ts.logBroadcast.Finish(runID)\n   277â†’\t}\n   278â†’\n   279â†’\t// Wait for process exit\n   280â†’\texitCode, err := s.container.Wait(ctx, containerID)\n   281â†’\tif err != nil {\n   282â†’\t\tlog.Printf(\"error waiting for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n   283â†’\t}\n   284â†’\n   285â†’\t// Extract step output files from container before it's removed\n   286â†’\toutputDst := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\")\n   287â†’\tif err := os.MkdirAll(outputDst, 0755); err == nil {\n   288â†’\t\tif cpErr := s.container.CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, \"/workspace/.cloche/output/.\", outputDst); cpErr != nil {\n   289â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract output: %v\", runID, cpErr)\n   290â†’\t\t}\n   291â†’\t}\n   292â†’\n   293â†’\t// Capture full container stdout/stderr before the container is removed\n   294â†’\tif logs, logErr := s.container.Logs(ctx, containerID); logErr == nil && logs != \"\" {\n   295â†’\t\tcontainerLogPath := filepath.Join(outputDst, \"container.log\")\n   296â†’\t\tif writeErr := os.WriteFile(containerLogPath, []byte(logs), 0644); writeErr != nil {\n   297â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to write container.log: %v\", runID, writeErr)\n   298â†’\t\t}\n   299â†’\t}\n   300â†’\n   301â†’\t// Index extracted log files in the log store\n   302â†’\tif s.logStore != nil {\n   303â†’\t\ts.indexLogFiles(ctx, runID, outputDst)\n   304â†’\t}\n   305â†’\n   306â†’\t// Extract results to git branch BEFORE finalizing state, so that\n   307â†’\t// WaitRun callers (e.g. host workflow merge step) see branches exist\n   308â†’\t// before the run is marked complete.\n   309â†’\tresultLabel := reportedResult\n   310â†’\tif resultLabel == \"\" {\n   311â†’\t\tif exitCode == 0 {\n   312â†’\t\t\tresultLabel = \"succeeded\"\n   313â†’\t\t} else {\n   314â†’\t\t\tresultLabel = \"failed\"\n   315â†’\t\t}\n   316â†’\t}\n   317â†’\t{\n   318â†’\t\textractRun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   319â†’\t\tif extractRun != nil && extractRun.BaseSHA != \"\" {\n   320â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: extracting results to branch cloche/%s (baseSHA=%s)\", runID, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA)\n   321â†’\t\t\tif err := docker.ExtractResults(ctx, containerID, extractRun.ProjectDir, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA, workflowName, resultLabel); err != nil {\n   322â†’\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract results to branch: %v\", runID, err)\n   323â†’\t\t\t} else {\n   324â†’\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: branch cloche/%s created successfully\", runID, runID)\n   325â†’\t\t\t}\n   326â†’\t\t} else {\n   327â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: skipping branch extraction (baseSHA empty or run not found)\", runID)\n   328â†’\t\t}\n   329â†’\t}\n   330â†’\n   331â†’\t// Now finalize run state\n   332â†’\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   333â†’\tif err != nil {\n   334â†’\t\treturn\n   335â†’\t}\n   336â†’\tif run.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   337â†’\t\tif reportedResult == \"succeeded\" {\n   338â†’\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   339â†’\t\t} else if reportedResult != \"\" {\n   340â†’\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n   341â†’\t\t} else if exitCode == 0 {\n   342â†’\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   343â†’\t\t} else {\n   344â†’\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"container exited with code %d\", exitCode))\n   345â†’\t\t}\n   346â†’\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   347â†’\t}\n   348â†’\n   349â†’\t// Fire evolution trigger if configured\n   350â†’\tif s.evolution != nil {\n   351â†’\t\ts.evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)\n   352â†’\t}\n   353â†’\n   354â†’\t// Merge is handled as a workflow step in host.cloche, not here.\n   355â†’\n   356â†’\t// Container retention policy:\n   357â†’\t// - Failed runs: always keep the container for debugging\n   358â†’\t// - Successful runs + --keep-container: keep the container\n   359â†’\t// - Successful runs without --keep-container: remove the container\n   360â†’\trunFinal, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   361â†’\trunFailed := runFinal != nil && (runFinal.State == domain.RunStateFailed || runFinal.State == domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   362â†’\n   363â†’\tif keepContainer || runFailed {\n   364â†’\t\treason := \"--keep-container\"\n   365â†’\t\tif runFailed {\n   366â†’\t\t\treason = \"run failed\"\n   367â†’\t\t}\n   368â†’\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: keeping container %s (%s)\", runID, containerID, reason)\n   369â†’\t\tif runFinal != nil {\n   370â†’\t\t\trunFinal.ContainerKept = true\n   371â†’\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, runFinal)\n   372â†’\t\t}\n   373â†’\t} else {\n   374â†’\t\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   375â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to remove container %s: %v\", runID, containerID, err)\n   376â†’\t\t} else {\n   377â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: removed container %s\", runID, containerID)\n   378â†’\t\t}\n   379â†’\t}\n   380â†’\n   381â†’\t// Cleanup mapping\n   382â†’\ts.mu.Lock()\n   383â†’\tdelete(s.runIDs, runID)\n   384â†’\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   385â†’}\n   386â†’\n   387â†’func (s *ClocheServer) ListRuns(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ListRunsRequest) (*pb.ListRunsResponse, error) {\n   388â†’\tfilter := domain.RunListFilter{\n   389â†’\t\tProjectDir: req.ProjectDir,\n   390â†’\t\tState:      domain.RunState(req.State),\n   391â†’\t\tTaskID:     req.TaskId,\n   392â†’\t\tLimit:      int(req.Limit),\n   393â†’\t}\n   394â†’\n   395â†’\t// When no project filter and not --all, default to last hour\n   396â†’\tif filter.ProjectDir == \"\" && !req.All {\n   397â†’\t\tfilter.Since = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour)\n   398â†’\t}\n   399â†’\n   400â†’\truns, err := s.store.ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter)\n   401â†’\tif err != nil {\n   402â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing runs: %w\", err)\n   403â†’\t}\n   404â†’\n   405â†’\tresp := &pb.ListRunsResponse{}\n   406â†’\tfor _, run := range runs {\n   407â†’\t\tresp.Runs = append(resp.Runs, &pb.RunSummary{\n   408â†’\t\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n   409â†’\t\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n   410â†’\t\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n   411â†’\t\t\tStartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n   412â†’\t\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n   413â†’\t\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n   414â†’\t\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n   415â†’\t\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n   416â†’\t\t\tProjectDir:   run.ProjectDir,\n   417â†’\t\t})\n   418â†’\t}\n   419â†’\treturn resp, nil\n   420â†’}\n   421â†’\n   422â†’func (s *ClocheServer) GetStatus(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetStatusRequest) (*pb.GetStatusResponse, error) {\n   423â†’\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   424â†’\tif err != nil {\n   425â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"getting run: %w\", err)\n   426â†’\t}\n   427â†’\n   428â†’\tresp := &pb.GetStatusResponse{\n   429â†’\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n   430â†’\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n   431â†’\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n   432â†’\t\tCurrentStep:  strings.Join(run.ActiveSteps, \",\"),\n   433â†’\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n   434â†’\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n   435â†’\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n   436â†’\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n   437â†’\t}\n   438â†’\n   439â†’\t// Check container liveness\n   440â†’\tif run.ContainerID != \"\" && s.container != nil {\n   441â†’\t\tif cs, err := s.container.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID); err == nil {\n   442â†’\t\t\tresp.ContainerAlive = cs.Running\n   443â†’\t\t\tif !cs.Running && !cs.FinishedAt.IsZero() {\n   444â†’\t\t\t\tresp.ContainerDeadSince = cs.FinishedAt.Format(time.RFC3339Nano)\n   445â†’\t\t\t}\n   446â†’\t\t}\n   447â†’\t}\n   448â†’\n   449â†’\t// Load step executions from captures store if available\n   450â†’\tif s.captures != nil {\n   451â†’\t\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n   452â†’\t\tif err == nil {\n   453â†’\t\t\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n   454â†’\t\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n   455â†’\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n   456â†’\t\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n   457â†’\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   458â†’\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   459â†’\t\t\t\t})\n   460â†’\t\t\t}\n   461â†’\t\t}\n   462â†’\t} else {\n   463â†’\t\tfor _, exec := range run.StepExecutions {\n   464â†’\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n   465â†’\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n   466â†’\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n   467â†’\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   468â†’\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   469â†’\t\t\t})\n   470â†’\t\t}\n   471â†’\t}\n   472â†’\n   473â†’\treturn resp, nil\n   474â†’}\n   475â†’\n   476â†’func (s *ClocheServer) StreamLogs(req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   477â†’\tctx := stream.Context()\n   478â†’\n   479â†’\t// Check for follow mode via gRPC metadata.\n   480â†’\tfollow := followFromContext(ctx)\n   481â†’\n   482â†’\t// Verify run exists\n   483â†’\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   484â†’\tif err != nil {\n   485â†’\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found: %w\", req.RunId, err)\n   486â†’\t}\n   487â†’\n   488â†’\t// If step_name or log_type filter is set, serve content directly from the log index\n   489â†’\tif req.StepName != \"\" || req.LogType != \"\" {\n   490â†’\t\treturn s.streamFilteredLogs(ctx, req, run, stream)\n   491â†’\t}\n   492â†’\n   493â†’\tisActive := run.State == domain.RunStateRunning || run.State == domain.RunStatePending\n   494â†’\n   495â†’\t// With -f on an active run: send existing logs then tail live output.\n   496â†’\tif follow && isActive && s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   497â†’\t\treturn s.streamFollowLogs(req.RunId, run, stream)\n   498â†’\t}\n   499â†’\n   500â†’\t// Without -f on an active run: snapshot existing logs and return.\n   501â†’\t// (Legacy callers that relied on implicit live streaming should use -f.)\n   502â†’\t// With -f on a completed run: same as without -f â€” no new lines will arrive.\n   503â†’\n   504â†’\t// Check for full.log first â€” if it exists, serve it as the unified log\n   505â†’\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   506â†’\tif data, readErr := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   507â†’\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   508â†’\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n   509â†’\t\t\tMessage: string(data),\n   510â†’\t\t}); err != nil {\n   511â†’\t\t\treturn err\n   512â†’\t\t}\n   513â†’\t\tif !isActive {\n   514â†’\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   515â†’\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   516â†’\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   517â†’\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   518â†’\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   519â†’\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   520â†’\t\t\t\treturn err\n   521â†’\t\t\t}\n   522â†’\t\t}\n   523â†’\t\treturn nil\n   524â†’\t}\n   525â†’\n   526â†’\tif s.captures == nil {\n   527â†’\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"captures store not configured\")\n   528â†’\t}\n   529â†’\n   530â†’\t// Fall back to capture-based streaming\n   531â†’\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n   532â†’\tif err != nil {\n   533â†’\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"getting captures: %w\", err)\n   534â†’\t}\n   535â†’\n   536â†’\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n   537â†’\t\t// Captures are stored as separate rows: one for step_started (no Result)\n   538â†’\t\t// and one for step_completed (has Result).\n   539â†’\t\tif exec.Result == \"\" {\n   540â†’\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n   541â†’\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_started\",\n   542â†’\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n   543â†’\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   544â†’\t\t\t}\n   545â†’\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n   546â†’\t\t\t\treturn err\n   547â†’\t\t\t}\n   548â†’\t\t} else {\n   549â†’\t\t\t// Read step output from per-step output file.\n   550â†’\t\t\t// Container runs write .log, host runs write .out â€” try both.\n   551â†’\t\t\tvar output string\n   552â†’\t\t\tfor _, ext := range []string{\".log\", \".out\"} {\n   553â†’\t\t\t\toutputPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", exec.StepName+ext)\n   554â†’\t\t\t\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   555â†’\t\t\t\t\toutput = string(data)\n   556â†’\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n   557â†’\t\t\t\t}\n   558â†’\t\t\t}\n   559â†’\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n   560â†’\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_completed\",\n   561â†’\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n   562â†’\t\t\t\tResult:    exec.Result,\n   563â†’\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   564â†’\t\t\t\tMessage:   output,\n   565â†’\t\t\t}\n   566â†’\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n   567â†’\t\t\t\treturn err\n   568â†’\t\t\t}\n   569â†’\t\t}\n   570â†’\t}\n   571â†’\n   572â†’\t// Send run completion entry\n   573â†’\tif !isActive {\n   574â†’\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   575â†’\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   576â†’\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   577â†’\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   578â†’\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   579â†’\t\t}); err != nil {\n   580â†’\t\t\treturn err\n   581â†’\t\t}\n   582â†’\t}\n   583â†’\n   584â†’\treturn nil\n   585â†’}\n   586â†’\n   587â†’// followFromContext checks for the follow flag in gRPC metadata.\n   588â†’func followFromContext(ctx context.Context) bool {\n   589â†’\tmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n   590â†’\tif !ok {\n   591â†’\t\treturn false\n   592â†’\t}\n   593â†’\tvals := md.Get(\"x-cloche-follow\")\n   594â†’\treturn len(vals) > 0 && vals[0] == \"true\"\n   595â†’}\n   596â†’\n   597â†’// streamFollowLogs sends existing log content then tails live output from the\n   598â†’// broadcaster. It combines snapshot + live streaming (like tail -f).\n   599â†’func (s *ClocheServer) streamFollowLogs(runID string, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   600â†’\t// Subscribe first so we don't miss lines written between read and subscribe.\n   601â†’\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n   602â†’\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n   603â†’\n   604â†’\t// Send existing full.log content if available.\n   605â†’\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   606â†’\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   607â†’\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   608â†’\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n   609â†’\t\t\tMessage: string(data),\n   610â†’\t\t}); err != nil {\n   611â†’\t\t\treturn err\n   612â†’\t\t}\n   613â†’\t}\n   614â†’\n   615â†’\t// Now tail live output from the broadcaster.\n   616â†’\tctx := stream.Context()\n   617â†’\tfor {\n   618â†’\t\tselect {\n   619â†’\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   620â†’\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n   621â†’\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   622â†’\t\t\tif !ok {\n   623â†’\t\t\t\t// Run completed â€” send terminal entry.\n   624â†’\t\t\t\tr, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n   625â†’\t\t\t\tif err == nil && r.State != domain.RunStateRunning && r.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n   626â†’\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   627â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   628â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(r.State),\n   629â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: r.CompletedAt.String(),\n   630â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   r.ErrorMessage,\n   631â†’\t\t\t\t\t})\n   632â†’\t\t\t\t}\n   633â†’\t\t\t\treturn nil\n   634â†’\t\t\t}\n   635â†’\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   636â†’\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n   637â†’\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n   638â†’\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n   639â†’\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n   640â†’\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   641â†’\t\t\t\treturn err\n   642â†’\t\t\t}\n   643â†’\t\t}\n   644â†’\t}\n   645â†’}\n   646â†’\n   647â†’// streamFilteredLogs serves log content filtered by step name and/or log type.\n   648â†’// It uses the log index when available, falling back to file path conventions.\n   649â†’func (s *ClocheServer) streamFilteredLogs(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   650â†’\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\")\n   651â†’\n   652â†’\t// Try log index first\n   653â†’\tif s.logStore != nil {\n   654â†’\t\tvar logFiles []*ports.LogFileEntry\n   655â†’\t\tvar err error\n   656â†’\n   657â†’\t\tif req.StepName != \"\" && req.LogType != \"\" {\n   658â†’\t\t\t// Filter by both step and type\n   659â†’\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n   660â†’\t\t\tif err == nil {\n   661â†’\t\t\t\tfiltered := logFiles[:0]\n   662â†’\t\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   663â†’\t\t\t\t\tif lf.FileType == req.LogType {\n   664â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tfiltered = append(filtered, lf)\n   665â†’\t\t\t\t\t}\n   666â†’\t\t\t\t}\n   667â†’\t\t\t\tlogFiles = filtered\n   668â†’\t\t\t}\n   669â†’\t\t} else if req.StepName != \"\" {\n   670â†’\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n   671â†’\t\t} else {\n   672â†’\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFileByType(ctx, req.RunId, req.LogType)\n   673â†’\t\t}\n   674â†’\n   675â†’\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n   676â†’\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   677â†’\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n   678â†’\t\t\t\tif readErr != nil {\n   679â†’\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   680â†’\t\t\t\t}\n   681â†’\t\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   682â†’\t\t\t\t\tType:     lf.FileType + \"_log\",\n   683â†’\t\t\t\t\tStepName: lf.StepName,\n   684â†’\t\t\t\t\tMessage:  string(data),\n   685â†’\t\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   686â†’\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n   687â†’\t\t\t\t}\n   688â†’\t\t\t}\n   689â†’\t\t\treturn nil\n   690â†’\t\t}\n   691â†’\t}\n   692â†’\n   693â†’\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n   694â†’\tif req.StepName != \"\" {\n   695â†’\t\tvar logPath string\n   696â†’\t\tswitch req.LogType {\n   697â†’\t\tcase \"llm\":\n   698â†’\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+req.StepName+\".log\")\n   699â†’\t\tdefault:\n   700â†’\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, req.StepName+\".log\")\n   701â†’\t\t}\n   702â†’\n   703â†’\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(logPath)\n   704â†’\t\tif err != nil {\n   705â†’\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"log file not found for step %q: %w\", req.StepName, err)\n   706â†’\t\t}\n   707â†’\t\treturn stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   708â†’\t\t\tType:     \"step_log\",\n   709â†’\t\t\tStepName: req.StepName,\n   710â†’\t\t\tMessage:  string(data),\n   711â†’\t\t})\n   712â†’\t}\n   713â†’\n   714â†’\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"no log files found matching filter\")\n   715â†’}\n   716â†’\n   717â†’// streamLiveLogs subscribes to the broadcaster and streams log lines in real\n   718â†’// time for an active run. The stream closes when the run completes or the\n   719â†’// client disconnects.\n   720â†’func (s *ClocheServer) streamLiveLogs(runID string, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   721â†’\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n   722â†’\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n   723â†’\n   724â†’\tctx := stream.Context()\n   725â†’\tfor {\n   726â†’\t\tselect {\n   727â†’\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   728â†’\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n   729â†’\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   730â†’\t\t\tif !ok {\n   731â†’\t\t\t\t// Run completed â€” send terminal entry.\n   732â†’\t\t\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n   733â†’\t\t\t\tif err == nil && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning && run.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n   734â†’\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   735â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   736â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   737â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   738â†’\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   739â†’\t\t\t\t\t})\n   740â†’\t\t\t\t}\n   741â†’\t\t\t\treturn nil\n   742â†’\t\t\t}\n   743â†’\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   744â†’\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n   745â†’\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n   746â†’\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n   747â†’\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n   748â†’\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   749â†’\t\t\t\treturn err\n   750â†’\t\t\t}\n   751â†’\t\t}\n   752â†’\t}\n   753â†’}\n   754â†’\n   755â†’func (s *ClocheServer) StopRun(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StopRunRequest) (*pb.StopRunResponse, error) {\n   756â†’\ts.mu.Lock()\n   757â†’\tcontainerID, ok := s.runIDs[req.RunId]\n   758â†’\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   759â†’\n   760â†’\tif !ok {\n   761â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found or already completed\", req.RunId)\n   762â†’\t}\n   763â†’\n   764â†’\tif err := s.container.Stop(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   765â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"stopping run: %w\", err)\n   766â†’\t}\n   767â†’\n   768â†’\t// Mark as cancelled in store\n   769â†’\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   770â†’\tif err == nil {\n   771â†’\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   772â†’\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   773â†’\t}\n   774â†’\n   775â†’\treturn &pb.StopRunResponse{}, nil\n   776â†’}\n   777â†’\n   778â†’func (s *ClocheServer) DeleteContainer(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DeleteContainerRequest) (*pb.DeleteContainerResponse, error) {\n   779â†’\tif s.container == nil {\n   780â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n   781â†’\t}\n   782â†’\n   783â†’\tid := req.Id\n   784â†’\tif id == \"\" {\n   785â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"id is required\")\n   786â†’\t}\n   787â†’\n   788â†’\t// Try to resolve as a run ID first\n   789â†’\tcontainerID := id\n   790â†’\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, id)\n   791â†’\tif err == nil {\n   792â†’\t\t// It's a run ID â€” use the container ID from the run record\n   793â†’\t\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   794â†’\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q has no associated container\", id)\n   795â†’\t\t}\n   796â†’\t\tcontainerID = run.ContainerID\n   797â†’\t}\n   798â†’\n   799â†’\t// Remove the container\n   800â†’\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   801â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"removing container: %w\", err)\n   802â†’\t}\n   803â†’\n   804â†’\t// If we resolved a run, clear the container_kept flag\n   805â†’\tif run != nil {\n   806â†’\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n   807â†’\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   808â†’\t}\n   809â†’\n   810â†’\treturn &pb.DeleteContainerResponse{}, nil\n   811â†’}\n   812â†’\n   813â†’func (s *ClocheServer) EnableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.EnableLoopRequest) (*pb.EnableLoopResponse, error) {\n   814â†’\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n   815â†’\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n   816â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n   817â†’\t}\n   818â†’\n   819â†’\t// Verify host.cloche exists\n   820â†’\thostPath := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", \"host.cloche\")\n   821â†’\tif _, err := os.Stat(hostPath); err != nil {\n   822â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"host.cloche not found in %s: %w\", projectDir, err)\n   823â†’\t}\n   824â†’\n   825â†’\t// Load project config for defaults.\n   826â†’\tprojCfg, _ := config.Load(projectDir)\n   827â†’\n   828â†’\tmaxConc := int(req.MaxConcurrent)\n   829â†’\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n   830â†’\t\tmaxConc = projCfg.Orchestration.Concurrency\n   831â†’\t}\n   832â†’\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n   833â†’\t\tmaxConc = 1\n   834â†’\t}\n   835â†’\n   836â†’\tstagger := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.StaggerSeconds)\n   837â†’\n   838â†’\t// Compute dedup timeout from config (default 5 minutes).\n   839â†’\tdedupTimeout := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.DedupSeconds)\n   840â†’\n   841â†’\tloopCfg := host.LoopConfig{\n   842â†’\t\tProjectDir:    projectDir,\n   843â†’\t\tMaxConcurrent: maxConc,\n   844â†’\t\tStaggerDelay:  stagger,\n   845â†’\t\tDedupTimeout:  dedupTimeout,\n   846â†’\t}\n   847â†’\n   848â†’\ts.mu.Lock()\n   849â†’\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n   850â†’\n   851â†’\t// Stop existing loop if running.\n   852â†’\tif existing, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n   853â†’\t\texisting.Stop()\n   854â†’\t}\n   855â†’\n   856â†’\t// Check if host.cloche defines a list-tasks workflow for three-phase mode.\n   857â†’\tvar loop *host.Loop\n   858â†’\tif s.hasWorkflow(hostPath, \"list-tasks\") {\n   859â†’\t\tloop = s.createPhaseLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, hostPath, dedupTimeout)\n   860â†’\t} else {\n   861â†’\t\tloop = s.createLegacyLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, projCfg, dedupTimeout)\n   862â†’\t}\n   863â†’\n   864â†’\ts.loops[projectDir] = loop\n   865â†’\tloop.Start()\n   866â†’\n   867â†’\treturn &pb.EnableLoopResponse{}, nil\n   868â†’}\n   869â†’\n   870â†’// hasWorkflow checks if host.cloche contains a workflow with the given name.\n   871â†’func (s *ClocheServer) hasWorkflow(hostPath, workflowName string) bool {\n   872â†’\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(hostPath)\n   873â†’\tif err != nil {\n   874â†’\t\treturn false\n   875â†’\t}\n   876â†’\treturn strings.Contains(string(data), fmt.Sprintf(\"workflow %q\", workflowName))\n   877â†’}\n   878â†’\n   879â†’// createPhaseLoop creates a three-phase orchestration loop using list-tasks,\n   880â†’// main, and finalize workflows from host.cloche.\n   881â†’func (s *ClocheServer) createPhaseLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir, hostPath string, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n   882â†’\t// Phase 1: list-tasks function\n   883â†’\tlistTasksFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string) ([]host.Task, error) {\n   884â†’\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   885â†’\t\t\tDispatcher: s,\n   886â†’\t\t\tStore:      s.store,\n   887â†’\t\t}\n   888â†’\t\ttasks, _, err := host.RunListTasksWorkflow(ctx, runner, projDir)\n   889â†’\t\treturn tasks, err\n   890â†’\t}\n   891â†’\n   892â†’\t// Phase 2: main function\n   893â†’\tmainFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   894â†’\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   895â†’\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   896â†’\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   897â†’\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   898â†’\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   899â†’\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   900â†’\t\t}\n   901â†’\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"main\")\n   902â†’\t}\n   903â†’\n   904â†’\t// Phase 3: finalize function (optional â€” only if host.cloche has it)\n   905â†’\tvar finalizeFn host.FinalizeFunc\n   906â†’\tif s.hasWorkflow(hostPath, \"finalize\") {\n   907â†’\t\tfinalizeFn = func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string, mainResult *host.RunResult) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   908â†’\t\t\tmainRunID := \"\"\n   909â†’\t\t\tmainOutcome := \"failed\"\n   910â†’\t\t\tif mainResult != nil {\n   911â†’\t\t\t\tmainRunID = mainResult.RunID\n   912â†’\t\t\t\tmainOutcome = string(mainResult.State)\n   913â†’\t\t\t}\n   914â†’\t\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   915â†’\t\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   916â†’\t\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   917â†’\t\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   918â†’\t\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   919â†’\t\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   920â†’\t\t\t\tExtraEnv: []string{\n   921â†’\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID=\" + mainRunID,\n   922â†’\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME=\" + mainOutcome,\n   923â†’\t\t\t\t},\n   924â†’\t\t\t}\n   925â†’\t\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"finalize\")\n   926â†’\t\t}\n   927â†’\t}\n   928â†’\n   929â†’\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: three-phase mode enabled for %s (list-tasks + main + finalize, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, dedupTimeout)\n   930â†’\treturn host.NewPhaseLoop(loopCfg, s.store, listTasksFn, mainFn, finalizeFn)\n   931â†’}\n   932â†’\n   933â†’// createLegacyLoop creates a legacy single-function orchestration loop.\n   934â†’func (s *ClocheServer) createLegacyLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir string, projCfg *config.Config, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n   935â†’\trunFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   936â†’\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   937â†’\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   938â†’\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   939â†’\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   940â†’\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   941â†’\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   942â†’\t\t}\n   943â†’\t\treturn runner.Run(ctx, projDir)\n   944â†’\t}\n   945â†’\n   946â†’\tloop := host.NewLoop(loopCfg, s.store, runFn)\n   947â†’\n   948â†’\t// Configure daemon-managed task assignment if a list-tasks command is set.\n   949â†’\tif cmd := projCfg.Orchestration.ListTasksCommand; cmd != \"\" {\n   950â†’\t\tloop.SetTaskAssigner(&host.ScriptTaskAssigner{Command: cmd})\n   951â†’\t\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: task assignment enabled for %s (command=%q, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, cmd, dedupTimeout)\n   952â†’\t}\n   953â†’\n   954â†’\treturn loop\n   955â†’}\n   956â†’\n   957â†’// GetLoopTasks returns the current task pipeline state for a project's\n   958â†’// orchestration loop, formatted as web.TaskEntry values. Returns nil if no\n   959â†’// loop is active for the project.\n   960â†’func (s *ClocheServer) GetLoopTasks(projectDir string) []web.TaskEntry {\n   961â†’\ts.mu.Lock()\n   962â†’\tloop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]\n   963â†’\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   964â†’\tif !ok {\n   965â†’\t\treturn nil\n   966â†’\t}\n   967â†’\tsnapshot := loop.GetTaskSnapshot()\n   968â†’\tentries := make([]web.TaskEntry, len(snapshot))\n   969â†’\tfor i, e := range snapshot {\n   970â†’\t\tentry := web.TaskEntry{\n   971â†’\t\t\tID:          e.Task.ID,\n   972â†’\t\t\tStatus:      e.Task.Status,\n   973â†’\t\t\tTitle:       e.Task.Title,\n   974â†’\t\t\tDescription: e.Task.Description,\n   975â†’\t\t\tMetadata:    e.Task.Metadata,\n   976â†’\t\t\tAssigned:    e.Assigned,\n   977â†’\t\t\tRunID:       e.RunID,\n   978â†’\t\t}\n   979â†’\t\tif !e.AssignedAt.IsZero() {\n   980â†’\t\t\tentry.AssignedAt = e.AssignedAt.Format(time.RFC3339)\n   981â†’\t\t}\n   982â†’\t\tentries[i] = entry\n   983â†’\t}\n   984â†’\treturn entries\n   985â†’}\n   986â†’\n   987â†’func (s *ClocheServer) DisableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DisableLoopRequest) (*pb.DisableLoopResponse, error) {\n   988â†’\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n   989â†’\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n   990â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n   991â†’\t}\n   992â†’\n   993â†’\ts.mu.Lock()\n   994â†’\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n   995â†’\n   996â†’\tif loop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n   997â†’\t\tloop.Stop()\n   998â†’\t\tdelete(s.loops, projectDir)\n   999â†’\t}\n  1000â†’\n  1001â†’\treturn &pb.DisableLoopResponse{}, nil\n  1002â†’}\n  1003â†’\n  1004â†’func (s *ClocheServer) Shutdown(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ShutdownRequest) (*pb.ShutdownResponse, error) {\n  1005â†’\t// Stop all orchestration loops.\n  1006â†’\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1007â†’\tfor _, loop := range s.loops {\n  1008â†’\t\tloop.Stop()\n  1009â†’\t}\n  1010â†’\ts.loops = make(map[string]*host.Loop)\n  1011â†’\ts.mu.Unlock()\n  1012â†’\n  1013â†’\tif s.shutdownFn == nil {\n  1014â†’\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"shutdown not configured\")\n  1015â†’\t}\n  1016â†’\tgo s.shutdownFn()\n  1017â†’\treturn &pb.ShutdownResponse{}, nil\n  1018â†’}\n  1019â†’\n  1020â†’// indexLogFiles scans the extracted output directory and creates log_files index entries.\n  1021â†’func (s *ClocheServer) indexLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID, outputDir string) {\n  1022â†’\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(outputDir)\n  1023â†’\tif err != nil {\n  1024â†’\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to read output dir for indexing: %v\", runID, err)\n  1025â†’\t\treturn\n  1026â†’\t}\n  1027â†’\n  1028â†’\tnow := time.Now()\n  1029â†’\tfor _, entry := range entries {\n  1030â†’\t\tif entry.IsDir() {\n  1031â†’\t\t\tcontinue\n  1032â†’\t\t}\n  1033â†’\t\tname := entry.Name()\n  1034â†’\t\tif !strings.HasSuffix(name, \".log\") {\n  1035â†’\t\t\tcontinue\n  1036â†’\t\t}\n  1037â†’\n  1038â†’\t\tvar fileType, stepName string\n  1039â†’\t\tbase := strings.TrimSuffix(name, \".log\")\n  1040â†’\n  1041â†’\t\tswitch {\n  1042â†’\t\tcase name == \"full.log\":\n  1043â†’\t\t\tfileType = \"full\"\n  1044â†’\t\tcase name == \"container.log\":\n  1045â†’\t\t\t// container.log is internal, not indexed as a user-facing log type\n  1046â†’\t\t\tcontinue\n  1047â†’\t\tcase strings.HasPrefix(name, \"llm-\"):\n  1048â†’\t\t\tfileType = \"llm\"\n  1049â†’\t\t\tstepName = strings.TrimPrefix(base, \"llm-\")\n  1050â†’\t\tdefault:\n  1051â†’\t\t\tfileType = \"script\"\n  1052â†’\t\t\tstepName = base\n  1053â†’\t\t}\n  1054â†’\n  1055â†’\t\tinfo, _ := entry.Info()\n  1056â†’\t\tvar fileSize int64\n  1057â†’\t\tif info != nil {\n  1058â†’\t\t\tfileSize = info.Size()\n  1059â†’\t\t}\n  1060â†’\n  1061â†’\t\tlogEntry := &ports.LogFileEntry{\n  1062â†’\t\t\tRunID:     runID,\n  1063â†’\t\t\tStepName:  stepName,\n  1064â†’\t\t\tFileType:  fileType,\n  1065â†’\t\t\tFilePath:  filepath.Join(outputDir, name),\n  1066â†’\t\t\tFileSize:  fileSize,\n  1067â†’\t\t\tCreatedAt: now,\n  1068â†’\t\t}\n  1069â†’\t\tif err := s.logStore.SaveLogFile(ctx, logEntry); err != nil {\n  1070â†’\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to index log file %s: %v\", runID, name, err)\n  1071â†’\t\t}\n  1072â†’\t}\n  1073â†’}\n  1074â†’\n  1075â†’func gitHEAD(dir string) string {\n  1076â†’\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\")\n  1077â†’\tcmd.Dir = dir\n  1078â†’\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n  1079â†’\tif err != nil {\n  1080â†’\t\treturn \"\"\n  1081â†’\t}\n  1082â†’\treturn strings.TrimSpace(string(out))\n  1083â†’}\n  1084â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HqGxcttN3K6oLdYWbW3TM7","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"1d61239c-5cdf-4517-a7d2-ee9a6a486dbe"}
