{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013xs6ZvdwjvkWEcjkCuqtgg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Workflows\n     2â†’\n     3â†’Cloche workflows define a directed graph of steps connected by named results.\n     4â†’\n     5â†’## Workflow Locations\n     6â†’\n     7â†’Cloche distinguishes two workflow locations based on the file they live in:\n     8â†’\n     9â†’**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) â€” Run inside a Docker\n    10â†’container via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type. These are the\n    11â†’standard workflows for coding tasks.\n    12â†’\n    13â†’**Host workflows** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) â€” Run on the host machine as the daemon\n    14â†’process. Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow` step type\n    15â†’dispatches a container workflow run and waits for it to complete. This is the extension\n    16â†’point for custom orchestration strategies.\n    17â†’\n    18â†’A single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n    19â†’uses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n    20â†’\n    21â†’| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n    22â†’|-------|--------------|---------|\n    23â†’| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n    24â†’| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n    25â†’| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n    26â†’\n    27â†’Only `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a legacy\n    28â†’single-function mode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n    29â†’\n    30â†’The `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n    31â†’object with the following fields:\n    32â†’\n    33â†’| Field | Required | Description |\n    34â†’|-------|----------|-------------|\n    35â†’| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n    36â†’| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n    37â†’| `title` | no | Short summary |\n    38â†’| `description` | no | Full description |\n    39â†’| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n    40â†’\n    41â†’The daemon picks the first task with status `open` (or empty, for backward\n    42â†’compatibility), runs `main` with that task ID, then runs `finalize` with the outcome.\n    43â†’Tasks are deduplicated within a configurable timeout window to prevent rapid\n    44â†’reassignment.\n    45â†’\n    46â†’The convention is enforced at parse time: a `workflow_name` step in a container workflow\n    47â†’file is a parse error.\n    48â†’\n    49â†’## Concepts\n    50â†’\n    51â†’| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n    52â†’|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n    53â†’| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    54â†’| step     | A unit of work (inferred: `prompt` = agent, `run` = script)        |\n    55â†’| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    56â†’| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step, with optional output mappings |\n    57â†’| done     | Built-in terminal step â€” successful completion                     |\n    58â†’| abort    | Built-in terminal step â€” failure with error reporting              |\n    59â†’\n    60â†’## Step Types\n    61â†’\n    62â†’Step type is inferred from the fields present in the step body:\n    63â†’\n    64â†’**agent** (has `prompt`) â€” Invokes a coding agent (Claude Code, or any tool conforming\n    65â†’to the agent adapter interface) with a prompt. The agent works autonomously inside the\n    66â†’container. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    67â†’\n    68â†’**script** (has `run`) â€” Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\n    69â†’any deterministic check. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    70â†’\n    71â†’**workflow** (has `workflow_name`) â€” Dispatches a named container workflow run and blocks\n    72â†’until it completes. Only available in host workflows (`host.cloche`).\n    73â†’\n    74â†’A step with more than one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`, or none of them, is a\n    75â†’parse error.\n    76â†’\n    77â†’## DSL Syntax\n    78â†’\n    79â†’```\n    80â†’workflow \"develop\" {\n    81â†’  container {\n    82â†’    image = \"my-project:latest\"\n    83â†’    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    84â†’  }\n    85â†’\n    86â†’  step implement {\n    87â†’    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    88â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    89â†’  }\n    90â†’\n    91â†’  step test {\n    92â†’    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n    93â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    94â†’  }\n    95â†’\n    96â†’  step fix {\n    97â†’    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    98â†’    max_attempts = \"3\"\n    99â†’    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   100â†’  }"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"d7b4f7ed-145c-4910-80c4-ac71a4b3007b"}
