{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014LoG1qS8a5eZi9fizGViCg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Installation\n     2â†’\n     3â†’This document covers the various ways to install Cloche on your machine.\n     4â†’\n     5â†’## Prerequisites\n     6â†’\n     7â†’All installation methods require:\n     8â†’\n     9â†’- **Docker** â€” Cloche runs workflows in containers\n    10â†’- **Git** â€” result extraction uses git worktrees\n    11â†’\n    12â†’## Build from Source\n    13â†’\n    14â†’Clone the repository, build the binaries and Docker image, and install them:\n    15â†’\n    16â†’```\n    17â†’git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    18â†’cd cloche\n    19â†’make install\n    20â†’```\n    21â†’\n    22â†’`make install` builds all three binaries (`cloche`, `cloched`, `cloche-agent`),\n    23â†’builds the `cloche-agent:latest` Docker image, installs the binaries to\n    24â†’`~/.local/bin/`, and starts the daemon. You can change the install prefix:\n    25â†’\n    26â†’```\n    27â†’make install PREFIX=/usr/local\n    28â†’```\n    29â†’\n    30â†’Make sure the install prefix is on your `PATH`:\n    31â†’\n    32â†’```\n    33â†’export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n    34â†’```\n    35â†’\n    36â†’### Build Requirements\n    37â†’\n    38â†’- Go 1.25+\n    39â†’\n    40â†’## `go install`\n    41â†’\n    42â†’If you have Go installed, you can install the binaries directly:\n    43â†’\n    44â†’```\n    45â†’go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest\n    46â†’go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloched@latest\n    47â†’go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche-agent@latest\n    48â†’```\n    49â†’\n    50â†’This places the binaries in `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin` by default).\n    51â†’\n    52â†’You still need to build the Docker image separately. Clone the repository and\n    53â†’run:\n    54â†’\n    55â†’```\n    56â†’git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    57â†’cd cloche\n    58â†’make docker-build\n    59â†’```\n    60â†’\n    61â†’## Pre-built Release Binaries (Planned)\n    62â†’\n    63â†’> **Note:** Pre-built release binaries are not yet available. This section\n    64â†’> describes the planned installation method for when releases are published.\n    65â†’\n    66â†’Download pre-built binaries from the\n    67â†’[GitHub Releases](https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases) page. Each\n    68â†’release will include archives for common platforms (Linux amd64, Linux arm64,\n    69â†’macOS amd64, macOS arm64).\n    70â†’\n    71â†’```\n    72â†’# Example: Linux amd64\n    73â†’curl -LO https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases/latest/download/cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    74â†’tar xzf cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    75â†’sudo install cloche cloched cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/\n    76â†’```\n    77â†’\n    78â†’You still need to build the Docker image. Clone the repo and run\n    79â†’`make docker-build`:\n    80â†’\n    81â†’```\n    82â†’git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    83â†’cd cloche\n    84â†’make docker-build\n    85â†’```\n    86â†’\n    87â†’## Homebrew (macOS / Linux) (Planned)\n    88â†’\n    89â†’> **Note:** A Homebrew tap is not yet published. This section describes the\n    90â†’> planned installation method.\n    91â†’\n    92â†’```\n    93â†’brew tap cloche-dev/tap\n    94â†’brew install cloche\n    95â†’```\n    96â†’\n    97â†’This will install all three binaries. You will still need the Docker image â€”\n    98â†’the formula will print post-install instructions for building or pulling it.\n    99â†’\n   100â†’## Verifying the Installation"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"d3a40b2f-b222-475f-9e51-a8d23dd1a057"}
