{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WqUzKRYV9ciVtWnhRkmqMa","type":"tool_result","content":"docs/workflows.md:30:The `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\ndocs/USAGE.md:279:Only `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\ndocs/USAGE.md:284:The `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\ndocs/USAGE.md:346:The `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\ndocs/USAGE.md:377:generated. As your project grows, you can add `list-tasks` and `finalize` workflows\ndocs/USAGE.md:391:The `list-tasks` workflow runs first. Its job is to query your task tracker (issue\ndocs/USAGE.md:693:With no arguments, lists all workflows grouped by type (container or host). With a\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:132:- `list-tasks` workflow runs are hidden from the Runs page (both server-rendered and\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md:23:# list_tasks_command = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md:36:- `orchestration.list_tasks_command` (optional) is a shell command that outputs a JSON array of\ndocs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init.md:215:  list                                        List all runs\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md:2775:\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing runs: %w\", err)\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md:3167:\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche <command> [args]\\n\\nCommands:\\n  run <workflow>  Launch a workflow run\\n  status <run-id> Check run status\\n  list            List all runs\\n  stop <run-id>   Stop a running workflow\\n\")\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md:3251:git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: wire cloche CLI with run/status/list/stop subcommands\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a"