{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JDqMpqRosYVGah9B6VJg4Y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Subdirectory Layout, Daemon-Side Extraction, and Poll Command\n     2â†’\n     3â†’**Date:** 2026-03-01\n     4â†’\n     5â†’## Overview\n     6â†’\n     7â†’Three related changes to Cloche:\n     8â†’\n     9â†’1. Move cloche project files into a `./cloche/` subdirectory of the host project, separating host-level files (CLAUDE.md, .git, build config) from agent-level files.\n    10â†’2. Replace the in-container git push mechanism with daemon-side result extraction using `docker cp` and host-side git operations (with worktrees for concurrency).\n    11â†’3. Add a `poll` command that blocks until a run reaches a terminal state or its container has been dead for >1 minute.\n    12â†’\n    13â†’## 1. Directory Layout\n    14â†’\n    15â†’### Host project (user's repo root)\n    16â†’\n    17â†’```\n    18â†’my-project/\n    19â†’â”œâ”€â”€ .git/\n    20â†’â”œâ”€â”€ .gitignore\n    21â†’â”œâ”€â”€ .gitworktrees/         # Daemon-managed git worktrees (gitignored)\n    22â†’â”œâ”€â”€ CLAUDE.md              # Host-level agent instructions\n    23â†’â”œâ”€â”€ README.md\n    24â†’â”œâ”€â”€ cloche/                # Everything cloche manages\n    25â†’â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ develop.cloche     # Workflow DSL file(s)\n    26â†’â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Dockerfile\n    27â†’â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ CLAUDE.md          # Inner agent instructions\n    28â†’â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ .cloche/\n    29â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ config\n    30â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ prompts/\n    31â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ implement.md\n    32â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ fix.md\n    33â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ <run-id>/      # Per-run output (gitignored)\n    34â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ prompt.txt\n    35â†’â”‚   â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ output/\n    36â†’â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ ...\n    37â†’â”‚   â””â”€â”€ <source files>     # Project code the agent works on\n    38â†’â””â”€â”€ <host-level files>\n    39â†’```\n    40â†’\n    41â†’### Inside the container\n    42â†’\n    43â†’```\n    44â†’/workspace/                # = contents of host's ./cloche/\n    45â†’â”œâ”€â”€ develop.cloche\n    46â†’â”œâ”€â”€ Dockerfile\n    47â†’â”œâ”€â”€ CLAUDE.md\n    48â†’â”œâ”€â”€ .cloche/\n    49â†’â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ config\n    50â†’â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ prompts/\n    51â†’â”‚   â””â”€â”€ ...\n    52â†’â””â”€â”€ <source files>\n    53â†’```\n    54â†’\n    55â†’The container sees a flat `/workspace/` â€” the contents of `./cloche/` are copied directly, not nested.\n    56â†’\n    57â†’### Gitignore additions\n    58â†’\n    59â†’`cloche init` adds to the host `.gitignore`:\n    60â†’\n    61â†’```\n    62â†’cloche/.cloche/*/\n    63â†’.gitworktrees/\n    64â†’```\n    65â†’\n    66â†’This ignores per-run output directories and worktrees, but keeps `cloche/.cloche/config` and `cloche/.cloche/prompts/` tracked.\n    67â†’\n    68â†’## 2. Container Lifecycle and Result Extraction\n    69â†’\n    70â†’### Run start\n    71â†’\n    72â†’1. The daemon records `base_sha` = current HEAD of the host repo.\n    73â†’2. `base_sha` is stored in the run record (new column in SQLite `runs` table).\n    74â†’3. `docker cp <host>/cloche/. <container>:/workspace/`\n    75â†’4. Container starts; agent runs the workflow autonomously.\n    76â†’\n    77â†’### Run completion\n    78â†’\n    79â†’When the container exits (success or failure):\n    80â†’\n    81â†’1. **Copy out:** `docker cp <container>:/workspace/. <tempdir>/`\n    82â†’2. **Create worktree:** `git worktree add --detach <project>/.gitworktrees/cloche/<run-id> <base_sha>`\n    83â†’3. **Populate:** Copy `<tempdir>` contents into `<worktree>/cloche/`\n    84â†’4. **Commit:**\n    85â†’   - `git checkout -b cloche/<run-id>` (in the worktree)\n    86â†’   - `git add cloche/`\n    87â†’   - `git commit -m \"cloche run <run-id>: <workflow-name> (<result>)\"`\n    88â†’5. **Cleanup:**\n    89â†’   - `git worktree remove <worktree-dir>`\n    90â†’   - Remove temp dir\n    91â†’   - Remove container (unless `--keep-container`)\n    92â†’\n    93â†’### Concurrency\n    94â†’\n    95â†’Each extraction uses its own git worktree at `<project>/.gitworktrees/cloche/<run-id>/`. Multiple extractions can run concurrently with no locking.\n    96â†’\n    97â†’### Error handling\n    98â†’\n    99â†’- If the container crashes, still attempt `docker cp` (the container filesystem persists until `docker rm`).\n   100â†’- If git operations fail, log the error, keep the container for debugging, and don't delete the temp dir.\n   101â†’\n   102â†’## 3. Poll Command\n   103â†’\n   104â†’### Usage\n   105â†’\n   106â†’```\n   107â†’cloche poll <run-id>\n   108â†’```\n   109â†’\n   110â†’### Behavior\n   111â†’\n   112â†’1. Connects to daemon via gRPC.\n   113â†’2. Polls `GetStatus(<run-id>)` every 2 seconds.\n   114â†’3. Prints status changes as they happen:\n   115â†’\n   116â†’```\n   117â†’[12:03:45] Run abc123 is running\n   118â†’[12:03:45] Step \"implement\" started\n   119â†’[12:04:12] Step \"implement\" completed: success\n   120â†’[12:04:12] Step \"test\" started\n   121â†’[12:04:30] Step \"test\" completed: fail\n   122â†’[12:04:30] Step \"fix\" started\n   123â†’[12:05:01] Step \"fix\" completed: success\n   124â†’[12:05:01] Step \"test\" started (retry)\n   125â†’[12:05:15] Step \"test\" completed: success\n   126â†’[12:05:15] Run abc123 succeeded\n   127â†’```\n   128â†’\n   129â†’4. Exits when:\n   130â†’   - The run reaches a terminal state (succeeded, failed, cancelled), **or**\n   131â†’   - The associated container has been dead (or never started) for >1 minute.\n   132â†’\n   133â†’### Exit codes\n   134â†’\n   135â†’- `0` â€” run succeeded\n   136â†’- `1` â€” everything else (failed, cancelled, container dead)\n   137â†’\n   138â†’### Protocol changes\n   139â†’\n   140â†’Add to the `GetStatusResponse` proto:\n   141â†’- `bool container_alive` â€” whether the Docker container is currently running\n   142â†’- `google.protobuf.Timestamp container_dead_since` â€” when the container was last seen alive (if dead)\n   143â†’\n   144â†’The daemon checks Docker container state when responding to status requests.\n   145â†’\n   146â†’## 4. Changes to `cloche init`\n   147â†’\n   148â†’`cloche init` now scaffolds into `./cloche/`:\n   149â†’\n   150â†’1. Creates `./cloche/` directory."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"b5d4215a-9fc3-4916-895c-35a3c4c79eb7"}
