{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W3oqHn3ZNfNzjw5YhFJLYC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# `cloche init` Implementation Plan\n     2â†’\n     3â†’> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n     4â†’\n     5â†’**Goal:** Add a `cloche init` command that scaffolds a Cloche project (workflow, Dockerfile, prompt templates) in the current directory.\n     6â†’\n     7â†’**Architecture:** New `init` case in the CLI's main switch, dispatching to `cmdInit()` in a new `cmd/cloche/init.go` file. Templates are string constants with `fmt.Sprintf` substitution. No daemon connection needed.\n     8â†’\n     9â†’**Tech Stack:** Go, `os` for file I/O, `fmt.Sprintf` for templating.\n    10â†’\n    11â†’---\n    12â†’\n    13â†’### Task 1: Create `cmd/cloche/init.go` with templates and `cmdInit()`\n    14â†’\n    15â†’**Files:**\n    16â†’- Create: `cmd/cloche/init.go`\n    17â†’\n    18â†’**Step 1: Write `cmd/cloche/init.go`**\n    19â†’\n    20â†’```go\n    21â†’package main\n    22â†’\n    23â†’import (\n    24â†’\t\"fmt\"\n    25â†’\t\"os\"\n    26â†’\t\"path/filepath\"\n    27â†’\t\"strings\"\n    28â†’)\n    29â†’\n    30â†’var workflowTemplate = `workflow \"%s\" {\n    31â†’  step implement {\n    32â†’    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    33â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    34â†’  }\n    35â†’\n    36â†’  step test {\n    37â†’    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    38â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    39â†’  }\n    40â†’\n    41â†’  step fix {\n    42â†’    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    43â†’    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    44â†’    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n    45â†’  }\n    46â†’\n    47â†’  implement:success -> test\n    48â†’  implement:fail -> abort\n    49â†’  test:success -> done\n    50â†’  test:fail -> fix\n    51â†’  fix:success -> test\n    52â†’  fix:fail -> abort\n    53â†’  fix:give-up -> abort\n    54â†’}\n    55â†’`\n    56â†’\n    57â†’var dockerfileTemplate = `FROM golang:1.25 AS cloche-builder\n    58â†’WORKDIR /src\n    59â†’COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n    60â†’RUN go mod download\n    61â†’COPY . .\n    62â†’RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o /cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n    63â†’\n    64â†’FROM %s\n    65â†’RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git nodejs npm && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    66â†’RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    67â†’COPY --from=cloche-builder /cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/cloche-agent\n    68â†’RUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\n    69â†’WORKDIR /workspace\n    70â†’RUN chown agent:agent /workspace\n    71â†’USER agent\n    72â†’`\n    73â†’\n    74â†’var implementPrompt = `Implement the following change in this project.\n    75â†’\n    76â†’## User Request\n    77â†’(Contents of .cloche/prompt.txt will be injected here by the adapter)\n    78â†’\n    79â†’## Guidelines\n    80â†’- Follow existing project conventions if files already exist\n    81â†’- Write tests for new functionality\n    82â†’- Run tests locally before declaring success\n    83â†’`\n    84â†’\n    85â†’var fixPrompt = `Fix the code based on the validation failures below.\n    86â†’Only modify files that need fixing. Do not rewrite the entire project.\n    87â†’\n    88â†’## Validation Output\n    89â†’(Contents of .cloche/output/*.log will be injected here by the adapter)\n    90â†’`\n    91â†’\n    92â†’func cmdInit(args []string) {\n    93â†’\tworkflow := \"develop\"\n    94â†’\timage := \"ubuntu:24.04\"\n    95â†’\n    96â†’\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n    97â†’\t\tswitch args[i] {\n    98â†’\t\tcase \"--workflow\":\n    99â†’\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   100â†’\t\t\t\ti++\n   101â†’\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n   102â†’\t\t\t}\n   103â†’\t\tcase \"--image\":\n   104â†’\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   105â†’\t\t\t\ti++\n   106â†’\t\t\t\timage = args[i]\n   107â†’\t\t\t}\n   108â†’\t\t}\n   109â†’\t}\n   110â†’\n   111â†’\tworkflowFile := workflow + \".cloche\"\n   112â†’\n   113â†’\t// Refuse to overwrite existing workflow\n   114â†’\tif _, err := os.Stat(workflowFile); err == nil {\n   115â†’\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %s already exists\\n\", workflowFile)\n   116â†’\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   117â†’\t}\n   118â†’\n   119â†’\t// Create prompts directory\n   120â†’\tif err := os.MkdirAll(\"prompts\", 0755); err != nil {\n   121â†’\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error creating prompts/: %v\\n\", err)\n   122â†’\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   123â†’\t}\n   124â†’\n   125â†’\t// Write all files\n   126â†’\tfiles := map[string]string{\n   127â†’\t\tworkflowFile:            fmt.Sprintf(workflowTemplate, workflow),\n   128â†’\t\t\"Dockerfile\":            fmt.Sprintf(dockerfileTemplate, image),\n   129â†’\t\t\"prompts/implement.md\":  implementPrompt,\n   130â†’\t\t\"prompts/fix.md\":        fixPrompt,\n   131â†’\t}\n   132â†’\n   133â†’\tfor path, content := range files {\n   134â†’\t\tif _, err := os.Stat(path); err == nil {\n   135â†’\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  skip %s (already exists)\\n\", path)\n   136â†’\t\t\tcontinue\n   137â†’\t\t}\n   138â†’\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(path, []byte(content), 0644); err != nil {\n   139â†’\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error writing %s: %v\\n\", path, err)\n   140â†’\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   141â†’\t\t}\n   142â†’\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  create %s\\n\", path)\n   143â†’\t}\n   144â†’\n   145â†’\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   146â†’\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"\\nInitialized Cloche project in %s\\n\", filepath.Base(cwd))\n   147â†’\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"\\nNext steps:\\n\")\n   148â†’\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  1. Edit %s â€” change the test command for your project\\n\", workflowFile)\n   149â†’\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  2. Edit Dockerfile â€” add your project's dependencies\\n\")\n   150â†’\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  3. docker build -t cloche-agent .\\n\")\n   151â†’\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"  4. cloche run --workflow %s --prompt \\\"...\\\"\\n\", workflow)\n   152â†’}\n   153â†’```\n   154â†’\n   155â†’Note: The `files` map iteration order is non-deterministic, but that's fine â€”\n   156â†’the output order of \"create\" messages doesn't matter.\n   157â†’\n   158â†’**Step 2: Verify it compiles**\n   159â†’\n   160â†’Run: `go build ./cmd/cloche/`\n   161â†’Expected: Compile error â€” `cmdInit` not wired into `main.go` yet. That's fine,\n   162â†’confirms the file parses.\n   163â†’\n   164â†’Actually this will compile since `cmdInit` is defined but not yet called.\n   165â†’Expected: Success, no errors.\n   166â†’\n   167â†’**Step 3: Commit**\n   168â†’\n   169â†’```\n   170â†’git add cmd/cloche/init.go\n   171â†’git commit -m \"feat(cli): add init command templates\"\n   172â†’```\n   173â†’\n   174â†’---\n   175â†’\n   176â†’### Task 2: Wire `init` into `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n   177â†’\n   178â†’**Files:**\n   179â†’- Modify: `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n   180â†’\n   181â†’**Step 1: Add `init` case to the switch and usage text**\n   182â†’\n   183â†’In `main()`, add the `init` case **before** the gRPC connection setup (since\n   184â†’init doesn't need a daemon). Restructure so that `init` is handled early:\n   185â†’\n   186â†’```go\n   187â†’func main() {\n   188â†’\tif len(os.Args) < 2 {\n   189â†’\t\tusage()\n   190â†’\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   191â†’\t}\n   192â†’\n   193â†’\t// Commands that don't need a daemon connection\n   194â†’\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n   195â†’\tcase \"init\":\n   196â†’\t\tcmdInit(os.Args[2:])\n   197â†’\t\treturn\n   198â†’\t}\n   199â†’\n   200â†’\t// Commands that need a daemon connection\n   201â†’\taddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\n   202â†’\t// ... rest unchanged\n   203â†’```\n   204â†’\n   205â†’Update `usage()` to include `init`:\n   206â†’\n   207â†’```go\n   208â†’func usage() {\n   209â†’\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, `usage: cloche <command> [args]\n   210â†’\n   211â†’Commands:\n   212â†’  init [--workflow <name>] [--image <base>]  Initialize a Cloche project\n   213â†’  run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"]      Launch a workflow run\n   214â†’  status <run-id>                             Check run status\n   215â†’  list                                        List all runs\n   216â†’  stop <run-id>                               Stop a running workflow\n   217â†’`)\n   218â†’}\n   219â†’```\n   220â†’\n   221â†’**Step 2: Verify it compiles**\n   222â†’\n   223â†’Run: `go build ./cmd/cloche/`\n   224â†’Expected: Success\n   225â†’\n   226â†’**Step 3: Commit**\n   227â†’\n   228â†’```\n   229â†’git add cmd/cloche/main.go\n   230â†’git commit -m \"feat(cli): wire init subcommand into CLI dispatch\"\n   231â†’```\n   232â†’\n   233â†’---\n   234â†’\n   235â†’### Task 3: Write tests for `cmdInit`\n   236â†’\n   237â†’**Files:**\n   238â†’- Create: `cmd/cloche/init_test.go`\n   239â†’\n   240â†’**Step 1: Write tests**\n   241â†’\n   242â†’```go\n   243â†’package main\n   244â†’\n   245â†’import (\n   246â†’\t\"os\"\n   247â†’\t\"path/filepath\"\n   248â†’\t\"testing\"\n   249â†’)\n   250â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"15838eb7-e667-4959-b447-00258653d9e6"}
