{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GkFczUUGiKuNd9x7G3e2uz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Project Pages Design\n     2â†’\n     3â†’**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4â†’**Status:** Design\n     5â†’\n     6â†’## Problem\n     7â†’\n     8â†’The projects landing page shows only health dots and a \"View Runs\" link. There is no\n     9â†’dedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\n    10â†’or buried in other views.\n    11â†’\n    12â†’## Goal\n    13â†’\n    14â†’Add a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with four panels:\n    15â†’\n    16â†’1. **Orchestrator control** â€” view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\n    17â†’2. **Project info** â€” Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\n    18â†’3. **Tasks** â€” live task pipeline view showing discovered tasks, their status, and assigned runs\n    19â†’4. **Workflow view** â€” read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\n    20â†’\n    21â†’## Route\n    22â†’\n    23â†’```\n    24â†’GET /projects/{name}\n    25â†’```\n    26â†’\n    27â†’`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\n    28â†’The handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\n    29â†’\n    30â†’Project cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}`. The project page\n    31â†’includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots) and a \"View all runs\" link to\n    32â†’`/projects/{name}/runs` for the filtered runs list.\n    33â†’\n    34â†’## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\n    35â†’\n    36â†’### Display\n    37â†’- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\n    38â†’- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\n    39â†’- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\n    40â†’\n    41â†’### API additions\n    42â†’\n    43â†’```\n    44â†’GET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\n    45â†’POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\n    46â†’POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\n    47â†’POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\"concurrency\": N}\n    48â†’```\n    49â†’\n    50â†’`GET` response:\n    51â†’```json\n    52â†’{\n    53â†’  \"enabled\": true,\n    54â†’  \"in_flight\": 1,\n    55â†’  \"concurrency\": 2\n    56â†’}\n    57â†’```\n    58â†’\n    59â†’The orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\n    60â†’`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\n    61â†’this flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\n    62â†’\n    63â†’Concurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\n    64â†’\n    65â†’The Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\n    66â†’interface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\n    67â†’`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\n    68â†’\n    69â†’## Panel 2: Project Info\n    70â†’\n    71â†’### Display\n    72â†’- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\n    73â†’  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\n    74â†’- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\n    75â†’  design). Display as `v3`.\n    76â†’- **Prompt files**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show:\n    77â†’  - Current file contents in a collapsible accordion\n    78â†’  - Git commit history (short SHA, date, message)\n    79â†’  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\n    80â†’\n    81â†’### API additions\n    82â†’\n    83â†’```\n    84â†’GET /api/projects/{name}/info\n    85â†’```\n    86â†’\n    87â†’Response:\n    88â†’```json\n    89â†’{\n    90â†’  \"docker_image\": \"ubuntu:24.04\",\n    91â†’  \"version\": 3,\n    92â†’  \"prompt_files\": [\n    93â†’    {\n    94â†’      \"path\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\",\n    95â†’      \"content\": \"Full text of the prompt file...\",\n    96â†’      \"history\": [\n    97â†’        {\"sha\": \"abc1234\", \"date\": \"2026-03-05\", \"message\": \"evolution: tighten scope\"},\n    98â†’        {\"sha\": \"def5678\", \"date\": \"2026-03-01\", \"message\": \"init\"}\n    99â†’      ]\n   100â†’    }\n   101â†’  ]\n   102â†’}\n   103â†’```\n   104â†’\n   105â†’Implementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\n   106â†’via `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\n   107â†’\n   108â†’```\n   109â†’GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\n   110â†’```\n   111â†’\n   112â†’Returns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\n   113â†’\n   114â†’## Panel 3: Tasks\n   115â†’\n   116â†’### Display\n   117â†’- Table showing discovered tasks: Task ID, Title, Status, Assigned (yes/no), Run link\n   118â†’- Status badges: `open` (running style), `closed` (succeeded style), other (pending style)\n   119â†’- Auto-refreshes every 5 seconds via polling\n   120â†’- Shows \"No tasks discovered\" when the project has no list-tasks output\n   121â†’\n   122â†’### API\n   123â†’\n   124â†’```\n   125â†’GET /api/projects/{name}/tasks\n   126â†’```\n   127â†’\n   128â†’Returns the task pipeline state for the project's orchestration loop.\n   129â†’\n   130â†’### Runs page changes\n   131â†’\n   132â†’- `list-tasks` workflow runs are hidden from the Runs page (both server-rendered and\n   133â†’  JS-rendered views)\n   134â†’- Runs with the same `task_id` are grouped under a task header row\n   135â†’- The task header shows an aggregate status badge (active statuses running/pending outweigh terminal ones; among terminal-only runs the most recently started determines the result)\n   136â†’- The `task_id` and `task_status` fields are included in the `/api/runs` JSON response\n   137â†’- Runs without a `task_id` appear ungrouped below task groups\n   138â†’\n   139â†’## Panel 4: Workflow View\n   140â†’\n   141â†’### Display\n   142â†’- Two-level tab navigation:\n   143â†’  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n   144â†’  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n   145â†’- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n   146â†’  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent ًں¤– / script ًں“œ / workflow ًں”پ)\n   147â†’  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n   148â†’  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n   149â†’- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n   150â†’  - Step name and type"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"c3564db5-fc08-4d7e-b96e-aaa720483469"}
