{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I have thoroughly searched the documentation. Let me provide a comprehensive report of all findings.\n\n## Summary of Documentation Files Referencing CLI Commands, Subcommands, Flags, and `cloche list`\n\nI've completed a thorough search of all documentation in the project. Here are all the files that reference `cloche list`, CLI commands, subcommands, and flags:\n\n### **Primary Documentation Files with CLI References:**\n\n1. **`/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go`** â€” Contains comprehensive help text for all CLI subcommands including `cloche list`. The help map includes:\n   - Detailed usage information for `list` command (lines 158-185)\n   - Describes flags: `--all`, `--project`, `--state`, `--limit`, `--issue`\n   - Lists output columns and provides examples\n   - Also documents other commands: `init`, `health`, `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `stop`, `delete`, `tasks`, `loop`, `get`, `set`, `workflow`, `shutdown`\n\n2. **`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`** â€” CLI entry point showing:\n   - Line 89-90: `list` registered as a daemon command requiring connection\n   - Main help dispatch logic starting line 32\n\n3. **`/workspace/README.md`** â€” Main project README with:\n   - Lines 113-122: Example of `cloche run`, `cloche status`, and `cloche logs` usage\n   - Lines 136-137: Link to USAGE.md documentation\n\n4. **`/workspace/CLAUDE.md`** â€” Project guidance file with:\n   - Line 19: Lists CLI subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop` (note: written before `list` was added, doesn't mention it)\n\n5. **`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`** â€” Comprehensive CLI reference with:\n   - Lines 628-634: Full `cloche list` command documentation including flags and examples\n   - Sections documenting: `cloche init`, `cloche run`, `cloche status`, `cloche logs`, `cloche poll`, `cloche stop`, `cloche delete`, `cloche health`, `cloche workflow`, `cloche get`, `cloche set`, `cloche tasks`, `cloche loop`, `cloche shutdown`\n\n6. **`/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`** â€” Installation guide with:\n   - Line 116: Example usage of `cloche list`\n\n7. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`** â€” MVP Design Document with:\n   - Lines 26-30: Original planned subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`\n   - Notes that `list` was not in original MVP scope (found in Post-MVP section line 244)\n\n8. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`** â€” Implementation plan with:\n   - Line 3167: Usage text showing `list` as one of the planned commands\n   - Line 3251: Commit message mentioning \"wire cloche CLI with run/status/list/stop subcommands\"\n\n9. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-23-cloche-init.md`** â€” Init command implementation plan with:\n   - Line 215: Mentions `list` command in the usage text example\n\n10. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-01-subdirectory-layout-and-poll-design.md`** â€” Poll command design with:\n    - Details poll command behavior (separate from list but related infrastructure)\n\n11. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** â€” Web UI design with:\n    - References to task/run listing on web pages\n\n12. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`** â€” Configuration file design with:\n    - References to `list_tasks_command` (for orchestration, different from `cloche list` command)\n\n### **Key Details About `cloche list` Command:**\n\nFrom `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 158-185):\n\n```\ncloche list â€” List workflow runs\n\nShows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\nwith --all. Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited\nto a fixed number.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche list [flags]\n\nFlags:\n  --all              Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n  --project, -p DIR  Filter by project directory.\n  --state, -s STATE  Filter by run state (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled).\n  --limit, -n NUM    Limit the number of results returned.\n  --issue, -i ID     Filter by issue/task ID.\n\nOutput columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\ntitle, container ID, and error message (if any).\n\nExamples:\n  cloche list\n  cloche list --all\n  cloche list --state running\n  cloche list --limit 10\n  cloche list --all --state failed --limit 5\n  cloche list --issue TASK-123\n  cloche list -p /home/user/project -s succeeded -n 20\n```\n\n### **All Documented Subcommands:**\n\nThe help.go file documents these CLI subcommands:\n- `init` â€” Initialize a Cloche project\n- `health` â€” Show project health summary\n- `run` â€” Launch a workflow run\n- `status` â€” Check run status\n- `logs` â€” Show logs for a run\n- `poll` â€” Wait for a run to finish\n- **`list`** â€” List workflow runs\n- `stop` â€” Stop a running workflow\n- `delete` â€” Delete a retained container\n- `tasks` â€” Show task pipeline and assignment state\n- `loop` â€” Manage the orchestration loop\n- `get` â€” Get a value from the run context store\n- `set` â€” Set a value in the run context store\n- `workflow` â€” View workflow definitions\n- `shutdown` â€” Shut down the daemon\n\n### **Files Without `cloche list` References:**\n\nMost documentation in `/workspace/docs/plans/` and other example files don't mention `cloche list` as they predate or focus on other features (evolution, initialization, host workflows, etc.)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8923f2c8f6123fad (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56141\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 34401</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"0e7bdcfa-d8e6-4a04-9393-b8ba7845124e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all documentation files in this project that might reference `cloche list`, CLI commands, subcommands, flags, or usage. C