{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CKYqsEEFkLEu8s8Va4cZVd","type":"tool_result","content":"   620â†’### `cloche status`\n   621â†’\n   622â†’```\n   623â†’cloche status <run-id>\n   624â†’```\n   625â†’\n   626â†’Shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   627â†’\n   628â†’### `cloche list`\n   629â†’\n   630â†’```\n   631â†’cloche list [--all]\n   632â†’```\n   633â†’\n   634â†’Lists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n   635â†’\n   636â†’### `cloche logs`\n   637â†’\n   638â†’```\n   639â†’cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   640â†’```\n   641â†’\n   642â†’| Flag | Description |\n   643â†’|------|-------------|\n   644â†’| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   645â†’| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   646â†’| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   647â†’\n   648â†’Without `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   649â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"12fdd603-536c-4d4f-b0f6-e665d77f267f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n","numLines":30,"startLine":620,"totalLines":828}}}
